Primitive datatypes used in Java
1. Integer – keyword of using integer datatype is int . it is of 4 bytes.
2. character – keyword is char. 2 bytes memory.
3. Boolean- used for true and false. Keyword- boolean It is of one bit.
4. short – keyword is short  and used for shorter integer range. Its memory size is 2 bytes.
5. Long- keyword is long and used for wide range of integer. Its memory size is 8 bytes.
6. float- float is used for decimal values and keyword is float. Its memory size is 4 bytes.
7.double- double is also used for decimal values but  has higher range than float. Its keyword is double and memory size is 8 bytes.
8. byte- byte has smaller inter range and it takes 2 byte of memory. Keyword is byte.
